io.github.cantido.qlearner.algorithm.model

Class ExplorationFactor

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Number
      • io.github.cantido.qlearner.algorithm.model.ExplorationFactor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    @Immutable
 @ThreadSafe
public final class ExplorationFactor
extends Number
    Represent's an agent's likelihood of taking non-optimal actions in order to explore the problem space.

    A value of 0.0 means that the agent should never explore, and a value of 1.0 means that the agent will always explore. How exactly your agent explores is decided by your ExplorationStrategy.
